            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> Caesar Vespas<lb break="no" n="2"/>ianus <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pontif</abbr><ex>ex</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> X <expan><abbr>imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/>XX co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan> IX <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ater</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>atriae</ex></expan> censor <lb n="5"/>viam <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustam</ex></expan> ab Iano <lb n="6"/>ad Oceanum refe<lb break="no" n="7"/>cit po<surplus>a</surplus>ntes fecit <lb n="8"/>veteres restituit
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Das Stück ist in 2 Teile gebrochen. Datierung: wohl zwischen Januar und März des Jahres 79 n. Chr., da die Designierung zum Konsul fehlt.</p>
            </div>
